Token.Abstract: A protocol implemented by the application to execute a custom tag.
Handler is given the tag name and a dictionary of named parameters.

Parameter.Name: tagName
Parameter.Abstract: The same name by which the handler was registered. It is provided as a convenience to allow a single handler to be registered for multiple function call tags.

Parameter.Name: parameters
Parameter.Abstract: The named parameters for the function call. The dictionary may contain NSString, NSNumber (double, int, or boolean), NSDictionary, or NSArray.

ReturnValue.Abstract: The evaluated result, which can be an NSString or NSNumber.
